<p><b>Tongan</b> (<i>lea fakatonga</i>) is an <a href="/wiki/Austronesian_languages" title="Austronesian languages">Austronesian</a> language spoken in <a href="/wiki/Tonga" title="Tonga">Tonga</a>. It has around 200,000 speakers and is a <a href="/wiki/National_language" title="National language">national language</a> of <a href="/wiki/Tonga" title="Tonga">Tonga</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> It is a <a href="/wiki/Verb_Subject_Object" title="Verb Subject Object">VSO</a> (Verb-Subject-Object) language.</p>
