<td bgcolor="#FFCC44">adverbial possessive</td>
<td bgcolor="#FFAA44">maʻane</td>
<td bgcolor="#AAFF44">moʻono</td>
<td bgcolor="#FFAA44">maʻana</td>
<td bgcolor="#AAFF44">moʻona</td>
<td bgcolor="#FFAA44">maʻanau</td>
<td bgcolor="#AAFF44">moʻonau</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Notes:</p>
<ol>
<li>the first syllable in all singular pronominal adjectives (in italics) is reduplicated and can be dropped for somewhat less emphasis</li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li>the pronominal adjectives put a stronger emphasis on the possessor than the possessive pronouns do</li>
<li>the use of the adverbial possessives is rare</li>
</ul>
<p>Examples of use:</p>
<ul>
<li>ko hono valá: it is his/her/its clothing/dress</li>
<li>ko e vala ʻona: it is his/her/its (!) clothing/dress</li>
<li>ko e vala ʻoʻona: it is his/her/its (!!!) clothing/dress</li>
<li>ko hono valá ʻona: it is his/her/its own clothing/dress</li>
<li>ko hono vala ʻoná: it is his/her/its own clothing/dress; same as previous</li>
<li>ko hono vala ʻoʻoná: it is his/her/its very own clothing/dress</li>
<li>ʻoku ʻoʻona ʻa e valá ni: this cloting is his/hers/its</li>
<li>ʻoku moʻona ʻa e valá: the clothing is for him/her/it</li>
<li>ʻoange ia moʻono valá: give it (to him/her/it) as his/hers/its clothing</li>
</ul>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Tongan_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Counting">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Counting">Counting</span></h2>
